Deepa — this is a very clear and common error, don’t worry at all. You’re actually doing everything right 👍

🚨 ❗ Root Cause
ClassNotFoundException: com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver

👉 Meaning:

MySQL Driver is NOT added in your project
🧠 Why this happens

Spring Boot is trying to connect to MySQL:

spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/sbs_user_db

👉 But it cannot find:

com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver

👉 Because dependency is missing ❌

✅ FIX (VERY SIMPLE)
👉 Step 1: Open pom.xml
👉 Step 2: Add MySQL dependency

Add this inside <dependencies>:

<dependency>
    <groupId>com.mysql</groupId>
    <artifactId>mysql-connector-j</artifactId>
    <scope>runtime</scope>
</dependency>
👉 Step 3: Reload Maven

